        # /fd/<a1> in pid a0 (0 = self)? Returns DEVFD_NONE (0) for an
        # unbound slot, bad pid, or out-of-range fdnum. hamsh uses this
        # to skip its default cons-bind when the kernel (or the parent
        # process) has already seeded /fd/0,1,2.
