        # is usable immediately (the next boot's sentinel parse re-adds it
        # from .hamnix-roots). ext4_useradd_root wrote to the ext4 root's
        # block slot; recover that slot and, from the by-id registry, the
        # partition's stable partuuid. The registry stores chan_ref ==
        # block slot for EVERY mounted partition (installed disk and LIVE
        # medium alike), so this works regardless of whether the root is
        # named `#sysroot` (installed) or `#distro` (LIVE) — the earlier
        # hard-wired `name_lookup_at("sysroot")` silently skipped the
        # name_push on the LIVE medium, leaving `#<name>` unresolvable
